Bandit 13 â†’ Bandit 14 

Objective

Log in to bandit14 using the private SSH key provided in bandit13, instead of a password.

Steps

1. Exit bandit13
bash exit

2. Copy the private SSH key to your local machine
bash scp -P 2220 bandit13@bandit.labs.overthewire.org:~/sshkey.private .

3. Fix file permissions
   SSH requires private keys to be readable only by the owner.
   bash chmod 600 sshkey.private

4. Log in using the private key
bash ssh -i sshkey.private bandit14@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220

5. Retrieve the password for bandit14
bash cat /etc/bandit_pass/bandit14

Result
successfully authenticated to bandit14 using key-based SSH authentication and retrieved the password for the next level.
